REQUIREMENTS
-----------------------------------
1)	You need to have a Java Development Kit (JDK) installed, as well as Simple
	Build Tool (SBT) for Scala to run the startup scripts. Alternatively, Eclipse or any other Java IDE with a Scala Plugin will do. 
		to Install SBT: http://www.scala-sbt.org/release/docs/Getting-Started/Setup.html#installing-sbt
		
2)	The software was tested with the following browsers:
	- Chrome 24+
	- Chromium 26+
	- Firefox 19+
	- Opera 12.14+
	- Internet Explorer 10+
	- Safari 6+
	If you experience any problems try updating your browser or use one of the browsers listed above.
	As this software uses the HTML canvas element and css flexbox, it is likely that this software will not run on older browser (especially IE prior to version 9).




INSTALLATION
-----------------------------------
1)	Extract all files of the ZIP / tar.gz / tar.bz2 file and copy the folder "ProcessManagement" anywhere you like.

3)	Start the Server
	3.1) SBT: run the startup.bat (Windows) or startup.sh (Unix) scripts in the Backend/ Folder.
	3.2) Eclipse / other IDEs: Open the Projekt and run the Boot.scala file as a Scala Application.

4)	You can now access the site via http://localhost:8080/sbpm

